snippet.textDisplay: If I was a non-European free agent, I'd much rather play in New Orleans than Dallas. With Lonzo, you'll get your opportunities on a regular basis, even with Zion and.B.I. Luka's usage rate is so high and then KP needs his touches, everyone else is getting scraps off the table. It's like going to play with Harden and Westbrook or Lebron and AD. The Pelicans have a more traditional, old school styled offense with a pass first PG. Other guys who are really skilled, can still get their shots there. Plus, you have that cultural familiarity. If you're a Black dude from DC, Philly, LA, NYC, Chicago or Detroit you're not going to have shyt in common with Luka or KP. Just keeping it a buck. After Mark Cuban discarded Dennis Smith Jr and Harrison Barnes like used toilet paper, any Black player landing in Dallas is relegated to be a background dancer status. So, no franchise level Black player would sign there, unless he was in denial about Cuban's intentions and team optics. That's only going to happen thru the draft or a trade most likely.
